Across FHIR versions, the element set has been mapped as:
* R5 `Permission` 0..* `Permission`

Following are the generation technical comments:
Element `Permission` is not mapped to FHIR R4, since FHIR R5 `Permission` is not mapped."/>

                  value="The data in scope are those with the given codes present in that data .meta.security element."/>
      <comment
               value="Note the ConfidentialityCode vocabulary indicates the highest value, thus a security label of &quot;R&quot; then it applies to all resources that are labeled &quot;R&quot; or lower. E.g. for Confidentiality, it's a high water mark. For other kinds of security labels, subsumption logic applies. When the purpose of use tag is on the data, access request purpose of use shall not conflict."/>

               value="Note the ConfidentialityCode vocabulary indicates the highest value, thus a security label of &quot;R&quot; then it applies to all resources that are labeled &quot;R&quot; or lower.
